Welcome back, Megan Bowen!

Each week, this email will give you an in-depth look at one of your work patterns
Focus Wellbeing Network Collaboration

Your Office 365 account includes MyAnalytics, a way to discover how you work

Your month in review: Focus

Do you have enough uninterrupted time to get your work done?

Available to focus

73%

Collaboration time

27%

"Available to focus" is an estimate of the time you have left over during working hours after meetings, emails, chats, and calls.
Discover more

Here's a closer look

Your past four weeks

Explore

Food for thought

You typically have 25% of your week spent in meetings. That's about 12 hours each week. Most of your weekly meetings are recurring.

Planning out when you'll do specific tasks can help you get more done. Try booking focus time in your calendar and adding tasks to the body of the appointment.
More insights

Explore More

Check your to-dos

Click on Insights in the Outlook ribbon to see your to-dos and more.

Find out where your time goes

Go to your dashboard to see who's in your network, how much you work after hours, and more.

Stay tuned for weekly summaries

Check back next week for your latest email digest.
